From 1fcccb790403f3a849181239b073a09049d256cd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Date: Tue, 20 Jan 2026 12:17:43 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] fix: sanitize absolute linkpaths properly (CVE-2026-23745)

This patch fixes a security vulnerability where absolute paths in linkpath
fields were not properly sanitized, allowing potential path traversal attacks
through hard links and symbolic links in tar archives.

The fix introduces a new STRIPABSOLUTEPATH method that validates and sanitizes
both 'path' and 'linkpath' fields by:
- Checking for '..' components in paths
- Stripping absolute path prefixes when preservePaths is false
- Applying consistent sanitization to both regular paths and link targets

This prevents attackers from using malicious tar archives to write files
outside the intended extraction directory through crafted linkpath values.

Backported from upstream commit: 340eb285b6d986e91969a1170d7fe9b0face405e
Security Advisory: https://github.com/isaacs/node-tar/security/advisories/GHSA-8qq5-rm4j-mr97

---
